election_record.label: Indiana 1824 Electoral College

sub_unit.name: Harrison
sub_unit.note: "In Harrison County five voters who intended to vote for Samuel Milroy gave the name as John Milroy." Indiana Election Returns.

sub_unit.name: Lawrence
sub_unit.note: "In Lawrence County five voters intended for Robb were given to David Gibson. The name had first appeared as Gibson in the newspapers but was later corrected. Robb was from Gibson County." Indiana Election Returns.

sub_unit.name: Madison
sub_unit.note: The November 30, 1824 edition of the American, and Commercial Daily Advertiser (Baltimore, MD) lists aggregate returns of 298 votes Andrew Jackson, 371 votes Henry Clay and 61 votes for John Quincy Adams.

sub_unit.name: Owen
sub_unit.note: David Gibson received two votes as David Robb.

sub_unit.name: Vanderburgh
sub_unit.note: "The returns for the Townships of Armstrong and Union have been lost." History of Vanderburgh County, Indiana. 67.
